dct_description_sm: Shows railways, roads, desert trails, communication lines, and in green, agricultural land. Eastern boundary line in Sinai Peninsula is marked by red defining the borders after reaching agreement between Egypt and Turkish (Ottoman) Empire, in April 8, 1892.
Relief shown by hachures and spot heights.
"London : Edward Stanford, Ltd. 12, 13, & 14, Long Acre, W.C."
